===Etymology===
(Northern form of) {{OE.}} {{term|ascian|āscian}}, from {{PG.}} *{{term||aiskōjan}}.  Cognate with German {{term|heischen}}.

===Pronunciation===
* (''[[Received Pronunciation|UK]]'') {{IPA|/ɑːsk/}}, {{SAMPA|/A:sk/}}
* (''[[General American|US]]'') {{IPA|/æsk/}}, {{SAMPA|/{sk/}}
* {{audio|en-us-ask.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑːks|-ɑːks]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# look for an [[answer]] to a [[question]] by [[speak]]ing.
# [[approach]] someone to do something.

====Usage notes====
* This is a [[catenative]] verb that takes the ''to infinitive''. See [[Appendix:English catenative verbs]]
* Pronouncing ask as /æks/ is a common example of [[methathesis]] and a feature of some varieties of English, notably [[African American Vernacular English]] (AAVE).

